The initial idea was pretty good, even though it came from a Twitter (then still Tumblr) diva. Originally the point was to subvert the stereotypical science fiction view of humanity as the default, with humanity's odd nature even on this planet in mind. That's all that stuff we take for granted in this general, like our endurance compared to other animals, our high speed over long distances, our ability to throw things much better than anything else on the planet. I don't think I've ever even seen the last one used. But like everything that becomes popular, idiots took over, and 90% of these stories became about our capacity for killing. In retrospect even some of the classics, like the Veil of Madness, are rather juvenile. But at least it's got a decent idea that's completely off the wall compared to mainstream science fiction, which was the point all along.
